# Strength sessions -- EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE

Copy this file to your Tempo content dir as `strength.md` (default
`<content_root>/strength.md`, redirect with `TEMPO_CONTENT_DIR`) and edit it.
Tempo reads it for S&C context in the recovery report (SC-03); it is never
committed (the content dir lives outside the repo tree).

## Format

One session per `## `-header block. The header carries the date (required),
optional start time, and optional name. Metadata lines and exercise bullets
sit beneath it. Parsing is lenient: unknown keys are silently ignored,
malformed lines are skipped, and a missing file degrades to `present=False`
so analyses still run. Append new sessions to the bottom -- the file is
treated as append-only by convention (Tempo never edits it).

**Header** -- `## YYYY-MM-DD [HH:MM] [— Name]`

- ISO date `YYYY-MM-DD` is required. Sessions with an unparseable date are
  dropped at parse time.
- Optional `HH:MM` (24-hour wall-clock start) immediately after the date.
- Optional ` — Name` (free-form session name). Either an em-dash `—` or a
  hyphen ` - ` separator is accepted.

**Metadata** (between header and the first exercise bullet, any order)

- `rest: M:SS` -- rest between sets, converted to seconds (`1:30` → 90).
  Malformed → `None`.
- `notes: <free text>` -- stored verbatim.
- Any other `key: value` line is silently ignored.

**Exercise bullets** -- `- <Name> [(Equipment)] [[GROUP]]: <set>, <set>, ...`

- `(Equipment)` -- optional annotation (`Barbell`, `Machine`, `Cable`,
  `Dumbbell`, `Leg Press`, ...). Stored verbatim. Bodyweight movements
  typically omit it.
- `[GROUP]` -- optional superset label (`[A]`, `[B]`, `[C1]`, ...). Two
  exercises in the same session sharing the same label are understood to
  be supersetted. Stored verbatim; the parser does not enforce pairing.
- `<set>` comes in three flavours:
  - **Weighted** `WxR` -- e.g. `55x8` → 55 kg × 8 reps. Lowercase `x`,
    uppercase `X`, and unicode `×` all accepted. Whitespace around the
    separator is fine (`55 x 8`).
  - **Timed hold** `M:SS` -- e.g. `1:00` → 60-second hold.
  - **Bodyweight reps** bare integer -- e.g. `15` → 15 reps unloaded.
- Anything that doesn't match those three is silently skipped.

